; Exhibit: why `proven` outranks `tested`. This property passes 200
; deterministic cases — the generator draws from [-20,20] plus boundary
; values, so testing will NEVER falsify it. Z3 refutes it in milliseconds
; with a counterexample far outside the sampled range.

(defn abs-small [] [(x Int)] Int
  (abs x)
  (prop bounded-wrongly [(x Int)]
    (<= (abs-small x) 400)))
